title: For Sale:  AK-74 5.45x39 Rifle
postcontent:
I bought a pair of AK74's a while back along with extra magazines and whatnot. I have since decided to sell one of them. One is unfired and the other has 60 rounds through it for function test (and then properly cleaned for corrosive ammo). You can pick which you like, but they are identical.
Anyways, they are the standard Century M74 with black plastic furniture, TAPCO trigger and other parts, 922 compliant with foreign magazines, etc. I added an ATI pistol grip (which is light years ahead of the standard grip) and picatinny rail (that mounts via standard AK style mounting pad that is riveted to the left side of the receiver). The rifle has the cleaning rod, bayo lug, screw-on AK74 style compensator/flash hider. I am including THREE proper (bulgarian?) magazines; not cheap TAPCO mags that do not fit correctly. The stock is also black plastic and is a tad longer than the typical AK47 wooden stock according to my judgment. It fits better, IMHO, unless you are wearing plates.
Yes, I have ammo, but it's cheap to buy right now, so I am not including any. You can buy milsurp in 1080 round spam cans for ~$135 according to my favourite ammo sites. Magazines are hard to come by though; that's why I am throwing in an additional pair beyond what the guns come with.
I am in central Ohio and will drive a little bit if necessary. Price is cash only to a 21 year old Ohio resident. I prefer CCW Licensee. If you have more questions please feel free to ask. Only trades I would consider are gold/silver, Saiga 12 or S&W 5.45x39 AR upper.
If you need more, I can also offer a package that includes ammo and a .50 Cal can, or more mags, but only to someone that buys the rifle. I will sell the ammo at replacement cost (only selling so you don't have to waste time waiting on ammo to shoot it) and mags at ~$20 apiece.


Cheers,
Mark

title: For Sale:  COLT DOUBLE EAGLE Series 90 45 ACP Stainless Double-Action 1911.
postcontent: Here's a Colt "Double Eagle, Series 90" pistol. This pistol is a modified 1911 with a double action (DA/SA) trigger lockwork and a frame mounted decocking lever. Chambered for the .45 ACP, this pistol is constructed of stainless steel and remains in excellent condition showing very little use. It is the full sized variation and the barrel measures 5" in length. There are no significant scratches or dings and I'd rate this pistol at 98% or better. Excellent bright bore and the mechanics are in good shape as well. It uses standard Colt 1911 type magazines so extras are easy to come by. This fine pistol comes with box, manual and paperwork (note: serial number on box differs from pistol).

title: For Sale:  COLT OFFICER'S MODEL .45 ACP SERIES 80 ULTIMATE BRIGHT STAINLESS
postcontent: This is a Colt Officer's Model Series 80 that's finished in Ultimate Bright Stainless. Chambered for the .45 ACP, this pistol remains unfired and in excellent condition. The Officer's Model is Colt's compact version of the famous 1911 Government Model. It features a slightly shorter grip frame and a 3-1/2" barrel. This pistol has the round "Commander" style hammer, slightly extended grip safety, flat serrated mainspring housing, and 3-dot sights. Condition is excellent to nearly mint. The mechanics are in perfect working order and the bore is new. Comes in the original box with owner's manual, hang tag, and all paperwork.
